      <Title>What is DocBook?</Title>
      <Para>DocBook is an XML based Document Type Definition (DTD) which 
            promotes a standard for exchanging documents independent of 
            their presentation.</Para>
      <Para>DocBook was developed primarily for exchanging Unix 
            documentation and is based on troff, a markup tool on Unix 
            and Linux platforms.</Para>
